.TH "DISPOSABLESTACK.DISPOSE" "3JS" "August 2, 2025" "JavaScript" "JavaScript Reference Manual"
.SH NAME
DisposableStack.dispose \- DisposableStack.prototype.dispose()
.SH SYNOPSIS
The \f[B]\f[CB]dispose()\f[B]\f[R] method of \f[CR]DisposableStack\f[R]
instances disposes this stack by calling all disposers registered to it
in reverse order of registration.
If the stack is already disposed, this method does nothing.
.PP
It performs the same action as
\f[CR]using disposer = new DisposableStack()\f[R] at scope exit.
It can be used if you need to clean up at a point other than scope exit.
.SH SYNTAX
.IP
.EX
dispose()
.EE
.SS Parameters
None.
.SS Return value
None (\f[CR]undefined\f[R]).
.SS Exceptions
.TP
\f[B]SuppressedError\f[R]
Thrown if multiple disposers in the stack threw an error.
If only one error is thrown, it is rethrown as\-is.
Otherwise, for each additional error, a new \f[CR]SuppressedError\f[R]
is created, with the original error as the \f[CR]suppressed\f[R]
property, and the new error as the \f[CR]error\f[R] property.
.SH EXAMPLES
.SS Disposing a stack
Here we push three disposers to the stack, using the \f[CR]use()\f[R],
\f[CR]adopt()\f[R], and \f[CR]defer()\f[R] methods.
When \f[CR]dispose()\f[R] is called, the disposers are called in reverse
order of registration.
.PP
Note that usually you don\(cqt need to call \f[CR]dispose()\f[R]
manually.
Declare the stack with \f[CR]using\f[R], and its
\f[CR][Symbol.dispose]()\f[R] method will be automatically called when
the stack goes out of scope.
.IP
.EX
\f[B]class\f[R] Resource {
  dispose() {
    console.log(\(dqResource disposed\(dq);
  }
  [Symbol.dispose]() {
    console.log(\(dqResource disposed via Symbol.dispose\(dq);
  }
}

{
  \f[B]const\f[R] disposer = \f[B]new\f[R] DisposableStack();
  \f[B]const\f[R] resource = disposer.use(\f[B]new\f[R] Resource());
  \f[B]const\f[R] resource2 = disposer.adopt(\f[B]new\f[R] Resource(), (resource) \f[B]=>\f[R]
    resource.dispose(),
  );
  disposer.defer(() \f[B]=>\f[R] console.log(\(dqDeferred disposer\(dq));
  disposer.dispose();
  \f[I]// Logs in order:\f[R]
  \f[I]// Deferred disposer\f[R]
  \f[I]// Resource disposed\f[R]
  \f[I]// Resource disposed via Symbol.dispose\f[R]
}
.EE
